ell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":50,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":59,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":94,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Alice de Merlay was born in 1165, in Derby, Derbyshire, England, her father, Roger de Merlay Lord Morpeth, was 25 and her mother, Alice de Stuteville, was 11. She had at least 1 son with Thomas de Dacre. She was buried in Lancashire, England."},"et":{"1165–":"1165–Surnud","1165–Female":"1165–Surnud","1180–1230":"1180–1230","–Male":"Surnud","1150–Male":"1150–Surnud","1180–Male":"1180–Surnud","1140–1188":"1140–1188","1154–1202":"1154–1202","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1202":"1202","about 1180":"umbes 1180","1188":"1188","1165":"1165","1154":"1154","1230":"1230","1140":"114